<subSubSection id="C33B07F8072CA23B53D2EEFEFDC84EA1" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="293" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9E5473072CA23B53D2EEFEFDC84EA1" blockId="7.[136,1452,1978,2077]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,158,400]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="293" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis id="B9558861072CA23453D2EEFEFFEA48E5" bold="true" box="[136,203,1978,2004]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072CA2345381EEFFFE4448E5" author="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G." box="[219,357,1978,2005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" pagination="91 - 93" refId="ref3929" refString="Nees Von Esenbeck, C. G. (1832) Acanthaceae Indiae Orientalis. In: N. Wallich (Ed.) Plantae Asiaticae rariores, or, Descriptions and figures of a select number of unpublished East Indian plants, 3. Treuttel et Wurtz, London, pp. 91 - 93." type="book chapter" year="1832">Nees (1832)</bibRefCitation>
validated 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF0072CA2345286EEFFFD6148E5" authorityName="Heyne ex Nees" authorityYear="1832" box="[476,576,1978,2004]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B9558861072CA2345286EEFFFD6148E5" box="[476,576,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the two gatherings distributed by Wallich ‘Herb. Madrasp. et Herb. Heyn. Wall. Cat. n. 2502a, b.’ without specifying the type. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB02982072CA2345079EE9AFBAA48C9" author="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R." box="[803,1163,2014,2040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292" pagination="81 - 130" refId="ref4246" refString="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R. (2010) Revision of the genus Barleria (Acanthaceae) in India. Rheedea 20: 81 - 130." type="journal article" year="2010">Shendage and Yadav (2010: 94)</bibRefCitation>
indicated “Wall., Numer. List No. 2502a (CAL)” as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD1072CA23452E1E146FD03472D" box="[443,546,2050,2076]" pageId="7" pageNumber="292">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name, but their lectotypification was ineffective, as it violates Art. 7.11 of the ICN. The original material for this name includes 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B507EE9DBFCEC4F89" box="[804,973,158,185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
mounted on the same sheet from Nees’s Herbarium at GZU, one (GZU000261736) labelled “2502 / 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B5075E986FB764FED" authority="Hb. Madr." authorityName="Hb. Madr." box="[815,1111,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B5075E986FCFB4FED" box="[815,986,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Barleria pilosa</emphasis>
Hb. Madr.
</taxonomicName>
/ e Courtallum” and the other (GZU000251702) “2502/b / Hb. Heyn. / e Courtallum”; 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B505EE9A3FC8A4E31" box="[772,939,230,257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at K (“a”: K001116225 &amp; “b”: K001116226) mounted together with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB029820723A23B52CCE84EFDAE4E14" author="Wallich, N." box="[406,655,266,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" pagination="75 - 76" refId="ref4597" refString="Wallich, N. (1830 a) A numerical list of dried specimens of plants, in the East India Companys Museum collected under the superintendence of Dr. Wallich of the Company's botanic garden at Calcutta. London, pp. 75 - 76." type="book chapter" year="1830">Wallich’s (1830a: 76)</bibRefCitation>
cut-out label and another (K000797788) with label “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C212FF00723A23B57A4E84EFFF04E78" authority="Heyne" authorityName="Heyne ex Nees" authorityYear="1832" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B95588610723A23B57A4E84EFA8A4E15" box="[1278,1451,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">Barleria pilosa</emphasis>
Heyne
</taxonomicName>
/ ‘Cuttalam’ 
<date id="FF9F72B30723A23B5236E86AFEC34E79" box="[364,482,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" value="1828-07">July 1828</date>
”; and 
<specimenCount id="9D279FFA0723A23B5176E86BFDF44E79" box="[556,725,302,329]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at CAL (“2502 / Hb. Madr.”: CAL0000072414 &amp; “2502 / Hb. Heyn.”: CAL0000033995). Instead of the specimen from CAL, we select the specimen from K (K001116226) as 
<typeStatus id="549AEAD10723A23B53D2E832FFCE4EA1" box="[136,239,374,400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">lectotype</typeStatus>
because it matches well with the protologue.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
